MONITORING MONGODB WITH MONITIS

Original Author: Arthur Tumanyan

Company: Netangels

Web Site: http://www.netangels.net

OVERVIEW:
---------
These scripts allow a user to easily get some monitoring around their MongoDB instance using Monitis.


INSTALLATION:

How to Install:
	
	Make sure you have MongoDB installed (mongostat required)
	Download <mongodb monitor>
	Cd <mongodb monitor>
	bash ./monitis-mongo-monitor [arguments]
	Enjoy!
	
How to uninstall:

	rm -rf <mongodb monitor>


DEPENDENCIES:

	Bourne Again Shell
	Mongostat utility
	Curl (required for monitis bash API)

OTHER:

	Change APIKEY & SECRETKEY in monitis_config according to your settings

USAGE: 
	monitis-mongo-monitor [user <username> pwd <password>] mode <daemon|plugin|uniq>  host <hostname> port <port> metrics <metric1,metric2,metricN>

ARGUMENTS:
	user - mongodb database user
	password - mongodb database password
	mode - monitor mode
		daemon -- just sends all metrics available every 10 seconds to the monitis server
		plugin -- works in plugin mode , outputs requested metric's values
		uniq -- works in individual mode, outputs specified metric value, value mining requested time and the difference from previous value
	host - mongodb database host
	port - mongodb database port
	metrics - metrics to be retrived. In modes other than uniq it can be comma separated list like "metric1",metric2,metricN

EXAMPLES:
	monitis-mongo-monitor (without arguments) -- it will send all the metrics values every 10 seconds
	monitis-mongo-monitor user mongouser \
				password secret \
				mode plugin \
				host mongoserverhost \
				port portnum \
				metrics "Insert",Delete  -- (case sensitive)
	monitis-mongo-monitor mode uniq metric "Insert" -- only one metric available at time
	
